ğŸŸ¦ US3 â€“ Display a persistent action bar with BACK and NEXT buttons

User Story

As a coach
I want to have permanent BACK and NEXT buttons
So that I can easily navigate between steps of the process

Description

A persistent action bar is displayed above the footer on all steps of the Return Hardware journey.

It contains:
	â€¢	BACK button: navigates to the previous step
	â€¢	NEXT button: validates the current step and moves forward

Behavior:
	â€¢	NEXT is disabled until the current step is valid
	â€¢	BACK does not reset previously entered data
	â€¢	The action bar is always visible
	â€¢	Header and action bar remain visible during error handling (modal or toast)

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN I am on a step of the Return Hardware process
THEN a persistent action bar with BACK and NEXT buttons is visible

WHEN the step is not valid
THEN the NEXT button is disabled

WHEN I click BACK
THEN I return to the previous step
AND previously entered data is preserved

WHEN I click NEXT
THEN the current step is validated
AND I move to the next step

WHEN an error modal or toast is displayed
THEN the header and action bar remain visible

Estimate

ğŸ•’ 1 day

